⚙️ Setup Steps
1. Clone the repository
Bash

git clone [https://github.com/aryy005/budget-box.git](https://github.com/aryy005/budget-box.git)
cd budget-box
2. Install dependencies
Bash

npm install
3. Configure Environment Variables
Create a .env file in the root directory and add your Supabase connection string. (Note: Use Port 6543 Transaction Mode for Vercel)

Code snippet

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION][.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true](https://.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true)"
4. Setup Database
Generate the Prisma client and push the schema to your database:

Bash

npx prisma generate
npx prisma db push
5. Run the Server
Bash

npm run dev
Visit http://localhost:3000 to see the app.
